Whee! ^^ Yes, I have *finally* returned! -blink- I'm on my moms s/n. -shirty eyes- I could easily change my parental controls. Very easily. I think I will, but i'm only going to give myself an hour a day. I need to limit myself. ^^

Ok, changed it. I also made it so people can e-mail me without it being deleted.. RARG, but yay that people can send me things now.. ^^ Yayness! ^^

Why isn't anyone ooonnnnn... -whinepout- I'm boorreeddd... Ok, Let's talk about today! ^^

1st Period - Not much there.. I'm such a pushover. -sighness- I let people copy my homework ALL the time.. I know I shouldn't, but I do,, -sighness- Oh well..

2nd Period - I'm always getting jolly ranchers in that class. o.o It's cause it's my favorite class, Art! Although, i'm quiet and special in math class, too.. But I don't get all A's.. 

3rd Period - Dude, Alan likes me? O.o But Elizabeth is nice. She's the one who told me that Alan supposedly likes me.. I'm never going to look at him the same way again.. I will always look at him with one eyebrow raised an speak to him in an old-fashioned manner. -laughs at herself-

4th Period - Um, not much there, either.. Pooja came over to talk to Melissa, who sits next to me, and I was talking to her beforehand.. I was kinda like,"Hey, I was talking to her.." Then Pooja was all like, "We're BEST FRIENDS. See the necklace? -shows me necklace that says Best on it- Melissa has Friends. -hugs Mel-" Mel: -smile- Me: "......" WHO THE HELL CARES ABOUT FRIENDSHIP NECKLACES?! Those were SOOOO two years ago. But, i'm proud of myself, because then I said, "I don't need a necklace to prove she's my friend." Then I turned away, and walked out of class (The bell had rung, luckily, so I made a dramatic exit ^^). Pooja's starting to annoy me now...

5th Period - I almost fell asleep. We wrote these friendly letts to 5th Graders, talking about Red Ribbon Week.. I wrote mine in the sparkly new gel pens I got *Yay!*. I love gel pens now, but my mom was like, "They make everything for right-handed people now.. What about us lefties, huhnh?! WHAT ABOUT US?!" Me: "*O.O* MOM, WATCH THE ROAD!" Mom: "*turns, swerves* ..... *O.O;;*" Haha.. My mom is depressed, though.. I'm going to go see a movie with her on Thursday, since she has the day off, and I have a half day.. We might go see Alfie, with Jude Law... Jude's a SMB. o.o *heart*

6th Period - Another example of Mr.Duke's weirdness. When we were getting into groups, he was like, "Come on everyone! Be quick! Be quick like bunnies!!" Everyone: "*O.O* .... -laugh-" Yeah.. Haha..

7th Period - We started weight room, and Lexa was like, "*;-;* I don't wanna do any of that stuff..", Since her Aunt Flo is here. I hate Aunt Flo, but she hasn't visted me in a while.. -ponders this- Maybe she hates me now? Yay, if she does! ^^

After School: My mom is depressed. She says it's the season. So, I washed her sheets, and cleaned, which made her happy. Plus the movie, so.. And I tried to make her laugh alot, too. I want Mama to be happy! -tear- I sounded like Shuichi right there.. O.o Not G Shuichi. Cuppa Tea Shuichi. ^^

I luff his luffer...

MWEE!!!!

Instead, he had her say she loved him & felt her hug 1 last time, then had her wear his helmet so that she would live even though it meant that he would die. We all have something to live for. There's noone who dosen't.
Why do I keep forgetting this?
I live for my friends.
Only them.

Why do people give up so easily?

It sickens me.

These people, who have something to live for, give up, saying they don't.
There will always be someone out they who loves you.

These people, who give up so easily.
These people, who have family that love them.
They say they have nothing.
Are they really so blind, so blind that they cannot see what is so plainly there?
The Love that these people give to them?

Whether you are blessed or cursed,
It makes no difference, you are still there, you are still living.

These people who kill themselves, hoping for a better life,
I doubt they will get a better life.

Think about it.

Isn't the population in China the greatest?
It's more likey they will end up there.

What about Africa? 
The dying, starving children?
It could be there.

Killing yourself is as pointless as you think your life is, the reason you wanted to.

Really, everything is pointless, if you look at it as if you will die one day.
Why not today, ne?
It might as well be.

I vow this to myself.. No matter what happens, i'm going to do it. Noone's going to stop me. It'm my mission--my goal.
